        <abstract> 
<p>Is burning to hear CD’s reaction to Wallace’s excellent paper on man ["Origin of human races and the antiquity of man", <hi rend="italic">J. Anthropol. Soc. Lond.</hi> 2 (1864): clviii–clxxxvi].</p> 
            <p>Wallace’s disclaimer of credit for natural selection is high-minded.</p>
